         <abstract>
            <p>The cumulative bivariate t-distribution associated with random variables T&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt; = X&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;/(S/k)&lt;sup&gt;1/2&lt;/sup&gt;, T&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; = X&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;/(S/k)&lt;sup&gt;1/2&lt;/sup&gt; is considered where X&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;, X&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; are bivariate normal with correlation coefficient ρ and S is an independent χ&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; random variable with k degrees of freedom. Representations in terms of series and simple, one-dimensional quadratures are presented together with efficient computational procedures for the special functions used in numerical evaluation.</p>
          </abstract>
